Programming log from Saturday October 20th 2019. I was home by 8 last night and spent the majority of the night programming. It was exhilarating.
* Put code for a scrolling card view to BrowseActivity.java * created BrowserAdapter.java to do the creating and binding work of the app * created EventData.java to define the data * created EventDataModel.java to model the domain * Did minor refactoring on MainActivity.java * Created menu_browse.xml * Put code in fragment_event_card.xml * Put code in activity_browse.xml * Created dimens.xml, added two dimension values * Added color values and string values for layouts
Followed this guide for most of it: https://www.journaldev.com/10024/android-recyclerview-android-cardview-example-tutorial
* I added a constraint layout to activity_event.xml * and extended AppCompatActivity in EventActivity.java * theres nothing to send to this activity. yet.
* added an imageview to activity_event, gotta see how to make this and the content description change to a diff drawable/string based on selected event
* activity_main.xml has a cute lil cloud background now uwu
* kmain activity buttons r wider now lol
* kmain activity buttons r wider now lol
*created final string BASE_URL in MainActivity.java bc idk where to start with consuming this api but i guess were gonna find out, honey
* forgot about this project, added a variable "String sessionid" to meetupDomain.java in the hopes that I'll work on this project at some point in the future * smh v on brand

* im tryna make a selected event in BrowseActivity.java send to that specific event's eventActivity.java page. * MainActivity.java has a button to send to EventActivity just to test * added .EventActivity to AndroidManifest.xml * to be clear this build is broken bc onclick BrowseActivity event, it does not send to EventActivity successfully.
* literally just had to change the intent destination activity * hows that for wednesday luck???? yes
* when you click on an even in BrowseActivity, it sends to EventActivty.java for that specific activity. YAY

* created SavedEventActivity.java ** this will be a list of saved events ** we will send to this from selecting an event in BrowseActivty.java ** we will also be querying the schema.sql to change that event's boolean "IS_SELECTED" field * created activity_saved_event.xml ** its a recycler view "holder" activity. ** just like acitvity_browse.xml * in EventActivity.java ** added margin values to everything ** changed the name of the button & the string it is set to * in activity_event.xml ** changed the name of the button as well as the string its set to ** added margin values to everything * EventData.java ** added a bunch of TODO items ** created methods to getSelectedEventCount(), selectEvent() {where an sql query to change the boolean IS_SELECTED feild in the table * strings.xml: changed the name and value of the last string * schema.sql: created the file, created a create statement for table EVENT_DATA * gradle updated so there's alot of stuff here.
* refactoring: renamed the toSavedEventButton
* now we have a MapActivity.java, activity_map.xml, its in the android manifest, and the build.gradle lines we need are there
* created toMapButton in main activity which sends to MapActivity.java
* created a button in eventActivity that sends to the map activity * in a future commit we'll send an extra with the intent to specify activity & the map will show us the location of the event.
* ¯\_(ツ)_/¯ * i am sorry.
* title on the main activity is larger now : * )

* EventActivity.java : added .putExtra( selectedItemId) (for the map activity ppl :thank u emoji: * MainActivity.java : renamed all the intents to activities after the destination Activity for debugging purposes * MapActivity.java : added intent.getExtra code, the extra is saved as a final int eventId, added a toast but its commented out (from debugging) * activity_map.xml : changed tools:context from .MapsActivity to .MapActivity * schema.sql : moved from values * AndroidManifest.xml : changed android:name of .MapAcivity (from .MapsActivity)
* MapActivity.java : commented out the getIntent line, so super.onCreate is first line of onCreate * AndroidManifest.xml : added meta-data tag with goo*gle_ma*ps_ke*y
added SavedEventActivity to android manifest :D android dev is such a gas! Sometimes I'm having so much fun I forget to push!
